  "name": "John 16:16–33",
  "localizedName": "John 16:16–33",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus told the disciples that they would be sad when he was gone. And then they would see him again and be happy."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The disciples didn’t understand what Jesus meant about dying and then coming back to life. But later they would remember his words and be full of joy."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Then they would believe Jesus fully. And they would fully trust God’s love for them."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "They would remember what Jesus taught them and boldly pray to God as their Father. They would ask him for everything they needed and know that he would answer."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus’ main message was that the disciples didn’t have to be afraid. They could have peace even when their lives were filled with trouble and hardship."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "This is because Jesus is stronger than everything that opposes God. He described this as having won the battle over the world."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
